50|$|A <b>bonus</b> <b>payment</b> {{is usually}} made to {{employees}} {{in addition to}} their base salary as part of their wages or salary. While the base salary usually is a fixed amount per month, <b>bonus</b> <b>payments</b> more often than not vary depending on known criteria, such as the annual turnover, or the net number of additional customers acquired, or the current value of the stock of a public company. Thus <b>bonus</b> <b>payments</b> can act as incentives for managers attracting their attention and their personal interest towards what is seen as gainful for their companies' economic success.|$|R
